Provide your answer with these fields.
- explanation: your evaluation of the scenario provided by the agent A.
- is_report_correct: whether the report is correct or not (true/false). True means there is a violation.
</response format>
<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call can write past the end of body_dyn when tool_params.medium is true and body_dyn_size is smaller than the combined lengths of body_header and body_footer. The code does not check that body_dyn_size >= MHD_STATICSTR_LEN_(body_header) + MHD_STATICSTR_LEN_(body_footer). In that case the subtraction body_dyn_size - (len(header)+len(footer)) underflows (size_t wrap), the filler loop and/or the final memcpy(body_dyn + pos, body_footer, MHD_STATICSTR_LEN_(body_footer)) will copy bytes beyond the allocated buffer, violating Rule 21.17. (If body_dyn_size >= len(header)+len(footer) the call is safe.)
</scenario>

